# Jam-Fi Desktop Launcher
#
# Puts the EXTERNAL attack card (wlan1 by default) into monitor mode
# using raw ip/iw commands, then launches the Jam-Fi interactive toolkit.
#
# No cards are protected anymore (all may go down when ASUS enters monitor mode).
# See: /home/will/bin/PROTECTED_WIFI_INTERFACES
#
# Monitor mode commands (example for external card):
#   sudo ip link set wlan1 down
#   sudo iw dev wlan1 set type monitor
#   sudo ip link set wlan1 up
#
# Then runs: sudo python3 jam_fi.py
#
# Features of Jam-Fi include:
#   - Deauthentication attacks (single + all clients)
#   - WPA handshake capture
#   - Evil Twin + captive portal credential harvesting
#   - Karma responder
#   - MITM injection + payload delivery
#   - CVE-based router exploitation
#   - Auto-Pwn mode
#
# Usage:
#   - Double-click to launch on wlan1 (external)
#   - Or run from terminal: /home/will/bin/jam-fi/launch.sh wlan1
#
# For authorized testing / research use only.
